{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0652c320eb2b863cd20c2a46bbf32775","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"From `src/clusterRefresh.ts` and `docs/CLUSTER_CACHE_SPEC.md §11`:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Git-aware diff skip (avoid unnecessary re-hashing)\n\n`findChangedFiles` (`src/clusterRefresh.ts:150-166`) re-hashes every evidence file on every call. A git diff on the scoped paths is a fast shortcut:\n\n```ts\nconst changedViaGit = execGitDiff(cwd, factsheetPaths);\nif (changedViaGit.length === 0) {\n  return { fresh: true, checked_via: \"git_diff\" };\n}\n```\n\nOnly fall through to full hash verification if git reports changes. Pure optimization — hashing remains the source of truth.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Per-fact staleness tracking (partial stale, not full stale)\n\nCurrently any changed evidence file marks the entire factsheet stale. Instead, track per-fact evidence membership:\n\n- When `findChangedFiles` returns a changed file, identify which facts reference it\n- Mark only those facts as `omitted_facts += 1` rather than the whole factsheet\n- The factsheet remains usable for unaffected facts, with a `partial_stale` status\n- Consults can proceed with a warning listing the affected facts\n\nImplementation point: `src/clusterRefresh.ts:51-66` (the rejection block) splits from blanket staleness into per-fact tracking.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Auto-promote `static_verified` → `llm_verified` on refresh\n\n`verify_only` mode never runs LLM verification, so a `static_verified` factsheet stays that way indefinitely even if its claims have semantically drifted.\n\nAdd an opt-in `refresh_mode: \"verify_and_promote\"`:\n```ts\nif (input.mode === \"verify_and_promote\" && factsheet.status === \"static_verified\") {\n  const llmResult = await verifyFactsheetWithLlm(claude, cwd, factsheet, \"focused\");\n  if (llmResult.rejectedFacts.length === 0) {\n    db.markClusterFactsheetFresh(factsheet.id, \"llm_verified\", \"llm_verified\");\n  }\n}\n```\n\nExisting `verify_only` callers are unaffected — this only activates on explicit opt-in."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":187,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2719,"cache_read_input_tokens":100505},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80e168c3-f7d3-48fb-8e86-0c3c3b4ba74a","uuid":"ccc8c938-8b84-4c2a-a8be-b9913ab64c6d"}
